Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper discusses the use of stylometric analysis to link tweets produced by the same author, which falls under the scope of natural language processing and computational linguistics. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper analyzes the linkability of tweets and the privacy implications of multiple accounts, which relates to the study of social networks and information diffusion. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering): The paper may also be relevant to software engineering, as it discusses the design and implementation of microblogging platforms and their impact on user privacy. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper touches upon the societal implications of microblogging and the privacy concerns of users, which falls under the scope of the intersection between computing and society. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper discusses the privacy implications of multiple accounts and the linkability of tweets, which may be relevant to the study of cryptography and security in online communication.
